abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Oct. 2 (UPI)  Mike Schmidt, the major league leader, hit his 46th home run of the season and Keith Moreland singled home Del Unser with the tie-breaking run in the seventh inning tonight to lift the Philadelphia Phillies to a 4-2 victory over the Chicago Cubs.

abstract: The New York Mets, surrounded by a record number of empty seats in Shea Stadium, defeated the Pittsburgh Pirates again yesterday. They did it before 1,754 cash customers, and thereby wiped out a low attendance mark that had lasted only one day.

abstract: BROOK PARK, Ohio, Sept. 29--Philip Jordan, a sparkplug salesman here, says he will vote for Ronald Reagan this November because "his past record shows that he might be able to do something about the economy." But he still worries, he says, that the Californian "doesn't have enough experience in foreign affairs."
